/-! ## Project-local Mathlib supplement ‚ÄĒ corepresentability of the sections functor

The sections functor `őď(V, -)` on `X.Modules` is corepresented by the Form-B object
`jShriekOU V`.  Consequently its right derived functors agree, degreewise, with those of the
Hom-functor `Hom(jShriekOU V, -)` ‚ÄĒ the homological half of the identification
`RŠĶ† őď(V, -) ‚ČÖ Ext^q(jShriekOU V, -)` (the deep "Bridge (1)/(2)" connecting the higher-direct-image
presheaf homology to absolute cohomology). -/

/-- **Naturality of `jShriekOU_homEquiv` in the coefficient sheaf** (reproduced here; the version
in `AbsoluteCohomology.lean` is `private`). Composing a map `jShriekOU V ‚ü∂ F‚āĀ` with `g : F‚āĀ ‚ü∂ F‚āā`
corresponds, under corepresentability, to applying `g` on sections over `V`. -/
private lemma jShriekOU_homEquiv_nat (V : TopologicalSpace.Opens X)
    {F‚āĀ F‚āā : X.Modules} (h : jShriekOU V ‚ü∂ F‚āĀ) (g : F‚āĀ ‚ü∂ F‚āā) :
    jShriekOU_homEquiv V F‚āā (h ‚Čę g)
      = (ConcreteCategory.hom (((Scheme.Modules.toPresheafOfModules X).map g).app (op V)))
          (jShriekOU_homEquiv V F‚āĀ h) := by
  have hs : sheafificationHomAddEquiv V F‚āā (h ‚Čę g)
        = sheafificationHomAddEquiv V F‚āĀ h ‚Čę (Scheme.Modules.toPresheafOfModules X).map g :=
      (PresheafOfModules.sheafificationAdjunction
        (ūĚüô X.ringCatSheaf.obj)).homEquiv_naturality_right h g
  change freeYonedaHomEquiv V _ (sheafificationHomAddEquiv V F‚āā (h ‚Čę g)) = _
  rw [hs, freeYonedaHomEquiv_apply, PresheafOfModules.comp_app, ModuleCat.comp_apply]
  rfl

/-- `Scheme.Modules.toPresheafOfModules X` is additive (it is the additive composite
`forget ‚čô restrictScalars (ūĚüô)`). Project-local instance so `sectionsFunctor` is additive. -/
noncomputable instance toPresheafOfModules_additive :
    (Scheme.Modules.toPresheafOfModules X).Additive :=
  inferInstanceAs (SheafOfModules.forget X.ringCatSheaf ‚čô
    PresheafOfModules.restrictScalars (ūĚüô X.ringCatSheaf.obj)).Additive

/-- The sections functor `őď(V,-) : X.Modules ‚•§ Ab` is additive. Project-local instance (the flat
triple composite does not infer additivity automatically). -/
noncomputable instance sectionsFunctor_additive (V : TopologicalSpace.Opens X) :
    (AlgebraicGeometry.sectionsFunctor V).Additive := by
  unfold AlgebraicGeometry.sectionsFunctor
  haveI i2 : (PresheafOfModules.toPresheaf X.ringCatSheaf.obj ‚čô
      (evaluation (TopologicalSpace.Opens X)ŠĶíŠĶĖ AddCommGrpCat).obj (op V)).Additive :=
    Functor.instAdditiveComp _ _
  exact Functor.instAdditiveComp _ _

/-- **The sections functor `őď(V,-)` is corepresented by `jShriekOU V`.** A natural isomorphism
`sectionsFunctor V ‚ČÖ preadditiveCoyoneda.obj (op (jShriekOU V))`, assembled from the additive
corepresentability bijection `jShriekOU_homEquiv` and its naturality. Project-local: the functorial
upgrade of `jShriekOU_homEquiv`, the geometric input to the absolute-cohomology bridge. -/
noncomputable def sectionsFunctorCorepIso (V : TopologicalSpace.Opens X) :
    AlgebraicGeometry.sectionsFunctor V ‚ČÖ preadditiveCoyoneda.obj (op (jShriekOU V)) :=
  NatIso.ofComponents
    (fun F => (AddEquiv.toAddCommGrpIso (jShriekOU_homEquiv V F)).symm)
    (by
      intro F‚āĀ F‚āā g
      ext s
      simp only [AddEquiv.toAddCommGrpIso, comp_apply, Iso.symm_hom, AddCommGrpCat.hom_ofHom,
        AddEquiv.coe_toAddMonoidHom]
      rw [AddEquiv.symm_apply_eq]
      change (ConcreteCategory.hom ((AlgebraicGeometry.sectionsFunctor V).map g)) s
        = jShriekOU_homEquiv V F‚āā ((jShriekOU_homEquiv V F‚āĀ).symm s ‚Čę g)
      rw [jShriekOU_homEquiv_nat V ((jShriekOU_homEquiv V F‚āĀ).symm s) g, AddEquiv.apply_symm_apply]
      rfl)

/-- **Right derived functors transport along a natural isomorphism of additive functors.**
Project-local: assembled from `NatTrans.rightDerived` of `ŌĄ.hom`/`ŌĄ.inv` and functoriality
(`NatTrans.rightDerived_comp`, `NatTrans.rightDerived_id`). -/
noncomputable def rightDerivedNatIso {C D : Type*} [Category C] [Category D] [Abelian C]
    [HasInjectiveResolutions C] [Abelian D] {F G : C ‚•§ D} [F.Additive] [G.Additive]
    (ŌĄ : F ‚ČÖ G) (n : ‚Ąē) : F.rightDerived n ‚ČÖ G.rightDerived n where
  hom := NatTrans.rightDerived ŌĄ.hom n
  inv := NatTrans.rightDerived ŌĄ.inv n
  hom_inv_id := by rw [‚Üź NatTrans.rightDerived_comp, ŌĄ.hom_inv_id, NatTrans.rightDerived_id]
  inv_hom_id := by rw [‚Üź NatTrans.rightDerived_comp, ŌĄ.inv_hom_id, NatTrans.rightDerived_id]

/-! ## Project-local Mathlib supplement ‚ÄĒ `Ext` transport along the spectrum equivalence (Need #1)

The whole-scheme spectrum isomorphism `U ‚ČÖ Spec őď(U,ūĚí™)` (`Scheme.isoSpec`, a genuine iso because
`U` is affine) induces an *equivalence* of module categories `U.Modules ‚ČĆ (Spec őď U).Modules`,
assembled from `Scheme.Modules.pushforward` along the iso and its coherences. An equivalence functor
is fully faithful, exact, and preserves injective objects, so
`Functor.mapExt_bijective_of_preservesInjectiveObjects` upgrades `Ext.mapExactFunctor` along it
to an *isomorphism* of `Ext`-groups. This transports the residual general-affine-open Serre
vanishing for `U` to the `Spec`-developed `affine_serre_vanishing_general_open`.

The pushforward-of-an-iso construction is generic in the scheme isomorphism `ŌÜ : X ‚ČÖ Y`. -/

/-- **A scheme isomorphism induces an equivalence of module categories.** For `ŌÜ : X ‚ČÖ Y`, the
pushforward `Scheme.Modules.pushforward ŌÜ.hom` is an equivalence with quasi-inverse the pushforward
along `ŌÜ.inv`; the unit/counit are supplied by the
`pushforwardId`/`pushforwardComp`/`pushforwardCongr` coherences. Project-local: Mathlib packages the
pushforward functor and its coherences but not the equivalence assembled from an iso (the genuine
equivalence used to transport `Ext` for Need #1). -/
noncomputable def Scheme.Modules.pushforwardEquivOfIso {X Y : Scheme.{u}} (ŌÜ : X ‚ČÖ Y) :
    X.Modules ‚ČĆ Y.Modules :=
  CategoryTheory.Equivalence.mk
    (Scheme.Modules.pushforward ŌÜ.hom) (Scheme.Modules.pushforward ŌÜ.inv)
    ((Scheme.Modules.pushforwardId X).symm ‚Č™‚Čę Scheme.Modules.pushforwardCongr ŌÜ.hom_inv_id.symm ‚Č™‚Čę
      (Scheme.Modules.pushforwardComp ŌÜ.hom ŌÜ.inv).symm)
    (Scheme.Modules.pushforwardComp ŌÜ.inv ŌÜ.hom ‚Č™‚Čę Scheme.Modules.pushforwardCongr ŌÜ.inv_hom_id ‚Č™‚Čę
      Scheme.Modules.pushforwardId Y)

/-- The functor of `pushforwardEquivOfIso ŌÜ` is (defeq) the additive `pushforward ŌÜ.hom`. -/
noncomputable instance pushforwardEquivOfIso_functor_additive {X Y : Scheme.{u}} (ŌÜ : X ‚ČÖ Y) :
    (Scheme.Modules.pushforwardEquivOfIso ŌÜ).functor.Additive :=
  inferInstanceAs (Scheme.Modules.pushforward ŌÜ.hom).Additive

/-- **`Ext` transport along a scheme isomorphism.** For `ŌÜ : X ‚ČÖ Y` and `A B : X.Modules`, the
equivalence `pushforwardEquivOfIso ŌÜ` (whose functor is fully faithful, exact, and injective-object
preserving) upgrades the additive map `Ext.mapExactFunctor` to an isomorphism of `Ext`-groups
`Ext A B n ‚ČÉ+ Ext (ŌÜ_* A) (ŌÜ_* B) n`, via `Functor.mapExt_bijective_of_preservesInjectiveObjects`.
Project-local: the `Ext`-isomorphism half of Need #1 (the spectrum-equivalence transport). -/
noncomputable def Scheme.Modules.pushforwardExtAddEquiv {X Y : Scheme.{u}} (ŌÜ : X ‚ČÖ Y)
    [EnoughInjectives X.Modules] (A B : X.Modules) (n : ‚Ąē) :
    CategoryTheory.Abelian.Ext A B n ‚ČÉ+
      CategoryTheory.Abelian.Ext ((Scheme.Modules.pushforwardEquivOfIso ŌÜ).functor.obj A)
        ((Scheme.Modules.pushforwardEquivOfIso ŌÜ).functor.obj B) n :=
  AddEquiv.ofBijective ((Scheme.Modules.pushforwardEquivOfIso ŌÜ).functor.mapExtAddHom A B n)
    (Functor.mapExt_bijective_of_preservesInjectiveObjects
      (Scheme.Modules.pushforwardEquivOfIso ŌÜ).functor A B n)

/-- **Need #1 ‚ÄĒ `Ext` transport along the whole-scheme spectrum equivalence.** For an affine scheme
`U`, the canonical iso `U ‚ČÖ Spec őď(U,ūĚí™)` (`Scheme.isoSpec`) induces, for every `q`, an isomorphism
`Ext^q_U(A, B) ‚ČÖ Ext^q_{Spec őď U}(ŌÜ_* A, ŌÜ_* B)`. In particular the residual `Ext` over `U` vanishes
iff its transport over `Spec őď U` does. Project-local target of `lem:modules_isoSpec_ext_transport`.

The remaining identification of the transported arguments ‚ÄĒ `ŌÜ_*(jShriekOU V) ‚ČÖ jShriekOU V'` for
`V'` the (affine) image open, and quasi-coherence of `ŌÜ_* H` ‚ÄĒ is handed off (see the task-result
file); it is orthogonal to this transport and is the geometric naturality of `j_!` under a scheme
iso. -/
noncomputable def modulesIsoSpecExtTransport (U : Scheme.{u}) [IsAffine U]
    [EnoughInjectives U.Modules] (A B : U.Modules) (n : ‚Ąē) :
    CategoryTheory.Abelian.Ext A B n ‚ČÉ+
      CategoryTheory.Abelian.Ext
        ((Scheme.Modules.pushforwardEquivOfIso U.isoSpec).functor.obj A)
        ((Scheme.Modules.pushforwardEquivOfIso U.isoSpec).functor.obj B) n :=
  Scheme.Modules.pushforwardExtAddEquiv U.isoSpec A B n

/-! ## Project-local Mathlib supplement ‚ÄĒ `Ext`-vanishing ‚üĻ coyoneda right-derived vanishing

The homological-algebra half of the relative-affine vanishing argument (Bridge (1)/(2) remainder).
The `q`-th right derived functor of the additive Hom-functor `Hom(P,-) = preadditiveCoyoneda(op P)`,
evaluated at `H`, is computed (via the chosen injective resolution `I‚ÄĘ` of `H`,
`InjectiveResolution.isoRightDerivedObj`) as the homology at degree `q` of the cochain complex of
abelian groups `n ‚Ü¶ (P ‚ü∂ I‚ĀŅ)`.  By `InjectiveResolution.extMk` / `extMk_eq_zero_iff`, that homology
*is* `Ext P H q`: a degree-`q` cocycle is a map `f : P ‚ü∂ Iq` with `f ‚Čę d = 0`, and it is a coboundary
iff the class `extMk f` vanishes in `Ext`.  Hence if every class of `Ext P H q` vanishes (`q ‚Č• 1`),
the Hom-complex is exact at `q` and the right-derived object is a zero object.  Project-local: Mathlib's
`Ext` is built on the derived category, not on `Functor.rightDerived`, so this bridge is absent. -/

/-- The differential of the Hom-cochain-complex `n ‚Ü¶ (P ‚ü∂ I‚ĀŅ)` (the image of a cochain complex `K`
under `preadditiveCoyoneda(op P)`) acts by post-composition with the differential of `K`. -/
private lemma preadditiveCoyoneda_mapHomologicalComplex_d_apply {C : Type*} [Category C]
    [Preadditive C] (P : C) (K : CochainComplex C ‚Ąē) (i j : ‚Ąē) (g : P ‚ü∂ K.X i) :
    (((preadditiveCoyoneda.obj (op P)).mapHomologicalComplex (ComplexShape.up ‚Ąē)).obj K).d i j g
      = g ‚Čę K.d i j := by
  rw [Functor.mapHomologicalComplex_obj_d]
  rfl

/-- **`Ext`-vanishing forces the coyoneda right-derived object to vanish.** If every class of
`Ext P H q` is zero (`q ‚Č• 1`), then `(Hom(P,-)).rightDerived q` is a zero object at `H`. The
homological-algebra bridge between the project's `Ext`-based Serre vanishing and the
`Functor.rightDerived` description of the higher-direct-image presheaf homology. Project-local. -/
lemma isZero_coyoneda_rightDerived_of_forall_ext_eq_zero {C : Type*} [Category C]
    [Abelian C] [HasInjectiveResolutions C] [CategoryTheory.HasExt C] (P H : C) (q : ‚Ąē) (hq : 0 < q)
    (hExt : ‚ąÄ e : CategoryTheory.Abelian.Ext P H q, e = 0) :
    IsZero (((preadditiveCoyoneda.obj (op P)).rightDerived q).obj H) := by
  obtain ‚ü®p, rfl‚ü© := Nat.exists_eq_succ_of_ne_zero hq.ne'
  refine IsZero.of_iso ?_ ((injectiveResolution H).isoRightDerivedObj
    (preadditiveCoyoneda.obj (op P)) (p + 1))
  set R := injectiveResolution H with hR
  refine HomologicalComplex.ExactAt.isZero_homology ?_
  rw [HomologicalComplex.exactAt_iff' _ p (p + 1) (p + 2) (by simp) (by simp),
    ShortComplex.ab_exact_iff]
  intro x‚āā hx‚āā
  have hf : x‚āā ‚Čę R.cocomplex.d (p + 1) (p + 2) = 0 := by
    rw [‚Üź preadditiveCoyoneda_mapHomologicalComplex_d_apply P R.cocomplex (p + 1) (p + 2) x‚āā]
    exact hx‚āā
  obtain ‚ü®g, hg‚ü© := (R.extMk_eq_zero_iff x‚āā (p + 2) rfl hf p rfl).mp (hExt _)
  refine ‚ü®g, ?_‚ü©
  rw [‚Üź hg]
  exact preadditiveCoyoneda_mapHomologicalComplex_d_apply P R.cocomplex p (p + 1) g

/-- **`[HasInjectiveResolutions C]` provides enough injectives.** The degree-`0` term of the chosen
injective resolution, with its quasi-iso unit, is an injective presentation. Project-local connector
(Mathlib derives `HasInjectiveResolutions` from `EnoughInjectives` + `Abelian`, not conversely);
needed to feed `[EnoughInjectives U.Modules]` to the spectrum `Ext`-transport from
`[HasInjectiveResolutions U.Modules]`. -/
lemma enoughInjectives_of_hasInjectiveResolutions {C : Type*} [Category C] [Abelian C]
    [HasInjectiveResolutions C] : EnoughInjectives C where
  presentation X :=
    ‚ü®{ J := (injectiveResolution X).cocomplex.X 0
       f := (injectiveResolution X).őĻ.f 0 }‚ü©

/-- **An isomorphism in the first `Ext`-argument transfers subsingletons.** If `Ext B Y q` is a
subsingleton and `ŌÜ : A ‚ČÖ B`, then so is `Ext A Y q` (every class is the `ŌÜ.hom`-precomposite of its
`ŌÜ.inv`-precomposite, which vanishes). Project-local: the contravariant `Ext`-functoriality packaged
for the Serre-vanishing transport along the `jShriekOU` transport iso. -/
lemma subsingleton_ext_of_iso_fst {C : Type*} [Category C] [Abelian C] [CategoryTheory.HasExt C]
    {A B : C} (ŌÜ : A ‚ČÖ B) (Y : C) (q : ‚Ąē)
    [Subsingleton (CategoryTheory.Abelian.Ext B Y q)] :
    Subsingleton (CategoryTheory.Abelian.Ext A Y q) := by
  refine ‚ü®fun a b => ?_‚ü©
  suffices h : ‚ąÄ z : CategoryTheory.Abelian.Ext A Y q, z = 0 by rw [h a, h b]
  intro z
  have hw : (Abelian.Ext.mk‚āÄ ŌÜ.inv).comp z (zero_add q) = 0 := Subsingleton.elim _ _
  have hz : z = (Abelian.Ext.mk‚āÄ ŌÜ.hom).comp
      ((Abelian.Ext.mk‚āÄ ŌÜ.inv).comp z (zero_add q)) (zero_add q) := by
    rw [Abelian.Ext.mk‚āÄ_comp_mk‚āÄ_assoc, ŌÜ.hom_inv_id, Abelian.Ext.mk‚āÄ_id_comp]
  rw [hz, hw, Abelian.Ext.comp_zero]

/- Planner strategy:
Part (1): `R^q j_* H` is the sheafification of `V ‚Ü¶ H^q(j‚ĀĽ¬ĻV, H)` (presheaf description
`higher_direct_image_presheaf`, Stacks 01XJ); for affine `V`, `j‚ĀĽ¬ĻV = U ‚ą© V` is affine (U affine,
X separated), so `affine_serre_vanishing` kills `H^q` for `q ‚Č• 1`; affine opens are a basis ‚áí
`R^q j_* H = 0`. Part (2): take an injective resolution `H ‚Üí I‚ÄĘ`; `j_* I‚ÄĘ` is a resolution of
`j_* H` (each `j_* I‚ĀŅ` is `j_*`-acyclic by (1)) and each `j_* I‚ĀŅ` is `f_*`-acyclic (same presheaf
+ Serre-vanishing argument on `U ‚ą© f‚ĀĽ¬ĻV`); so `j_* I‚ÄĘ` is an `f_*`-acyclic resolution of `j_* H`,
and the P4 acyclic-resolution comparison (`acyclic_resolution_computes_derived` /
`rightDerivedIsoOfAcyclicResolution`) with `G = f_*` gives `R^k f_*(j_* H) ‚ČÖ H^k(f_*(j_* I‚ÄĘ)) =
H^k((f‚ąėj)_* I‚ÄĘ) = R^k (f‚ąėj)_* H`, using `f_* ‚ąė j_* = (f‚ąėj)_*`. Blueprint:
`lem:open_immersion_pushforward_comp`. Source: Stacks `lemma-relative-affine-vanishing`.
-/

/-- **Higher direct images of an affine open immersion vanish** (part (1) of blueprint
`lem:open_immersion_pushforward_comp`; Stacks `lemma-relative-affine-vanishing`).

For an open immersion `j : U ‚Ü™ X` where `U` is affine and `X` is separated, the morphism
`j` is affine (since for any affine open `V ‚äÜ X`, `j‚ĀĽ¬ĻV = U ‚ą© V` is affine by separatedness).
Therefore `R^q j_* H = 0` for every `q ‚Č• 1` and every quasi-coherent `O_U`-module `H`.

Proof route: by `higherDirectImage_iso_sheafify_presheafHomology`, `R^q j_* H` is the
sheafification of `V ‚Ü¶ H^q(j‚ĀĽ¬ĻV, H)`. For affine `V`, `j‚ĀĽ¬ĻV = U ‚ą© V` is affine (`U` affine
+ `X` separated), and `affine_serre_vanishing` kills `H^q` for `q ‚Č• 1`. Since affine opens
form a basis, the presheaf homology is locally zero, and the site lemmas
`isZero_presheafToSheaf_obj_of_isLocallyBijective` (in `CechHigherDirectImage.lean`,
importable via `AffineSerreVanishing`) collapse the sheafification to zero. -/
private lemma isAffineHom_of_affine_separated (j : U ‚ü∂ X) [IsAffine U] [X.IsSeparated] :
    IsAffineHom j := by
  have hg : IsSeparated (terminal.from X) := Scheme.IsSeparated.isSeparated_terminal_from
  have hcomp : IsAffineHom (j ‚Čę terminal.from X) := by
    have he : j ‚Čę terminal.from X = terminal.from U := terminal.hom_ext _ _
    rw [he]; infer_instance
  exact IsAffineHom.of_comp j (terminal.from X)

/-- The sections-over-`j‚ĀĽ¬ĻW` functor on `U`-modules, `M ‚Ü¶ őď(W, j_* M) = őď(j‚ĀĽ¬ĻW, M)`,
realised as the composite `pushforward j ‚čô forget ‚čô restrictScalars ūĚüô ‚čô toPresheaf ‚čô eval(W)`.
Its `q`-th right derived functor applied to `H` is the absolute cohomology `HŠĶ†(j‚ĀĽ¬ĻW, H)`.
Project-local: a named composite so its additivity instance is synthesised once at the top
level (the 5-fold composite defeats in-proof instance search). -/
noncomputable def pushforwardSectionsFunctor (j : U ‚ü∂ X) (W : TopologicalSpace.Opens X) :
    U.Modules ‚•§ AddCommGrpCat :=
  Scheme.Modules.pushforward j ‚čô SheafOfModules.forget X.ringCatSheaf ‚čô
    PresheafOfModules.restrictScalars (ūĚüô X.ringCatSheaf.obj) ‚čô
    PresheafOfModules.toPresheaf X.ringCatSheaf.obj ‚čô
    (evaluation (TopologicalSpace.Opens X)ŠĶíŠĶĖ AddCommGrpCat).obj (Opposite.op W)

noncomputable instance pushforwardSectionsFunctor_additive
    (j : U ‚ü∂ X) (W : TopologicalSpace.Opens X) : (pushforwardSectionsFunctor j W).Additive := by
  unfold pushforwardSectionsFunctor
  -- The flat 5-fold composite defeats instance search; build it as an explicit `instAdditiveComp`
  -- chain (every individual factor is additive).
  haveI hpf : (Scheme.Modules.pushforward j).Additive := inferInstance
  haveI i4 : (PresheafOfModules.toPresheaf X.ringCatSheaf.obj ‚čô
      (evaluation (TopologicalSpace.Opens X)ŠĶíŠĶĖ AddCommGrpCat).obj (Opposite.op W)).Additive :=
    Functor.instAdditiveComp _ _
  haveI i3 : (PresheafOfModules.restrictScalars (ūĚüô X.ringCatSheaf.obj) ‚čô
      PresheafOfModules.toPresheaf X.ringCatSheaf.obj ‚čô
      (evaluation (TopologicalSpace.Opens X)ŠĶíŠĶĖ AddCommGrpCat).obj (Opposite.op W)).Additive :=
    Functor.instAdditiveComp _ _
  haveI i2 : (SheafOfModules.forget X.ringCatSheaf ‚čô
      PresheafOfModules.restrictScalars (ūĚüô X.ringCatSheaf.obj) ‚čô
      PresheafOfModules.toPresheaf X.ringCatSheaf.obj ‚čô
      (evaluation (TopologicalSpace.Opens X)ŠĶíŠĶĖ AddCommGrpCat).obj (Opposite.op W)).Additive :=
    Functor.instAdditiveComp _ _
  -- Instance search will not pick up `i2` automatically here, so we pass it explicitly.
  exact @CategoryTheory.Functor.instAdditiveComp _ _ _ _ _ _
    (Scheme.Modules.pushforward j) hpf _ _ _ _ i2

theorem higherDirectImage_openImmersion_acyclic [HasInjectiveResolutions U.Modules]
    (j : U ‚ü∂ X) [IsOpenImmersion j] [IsAffine U] [X.IsSeparated]
    (H : U.Modules) (hH : H.IsQuasicoherent) (q : ‚Ąē) (hq : 0 < q) :
    IsZero (higherDirectImage j q H) := by
  -- `j` is an affine morphism (open immersion of an affine into a separated scheme),
  -- so the preimage of every affine open `V ‚äÜ X` is the affine open `j‚ĀĽ¬ĻV = U ‚ą© V`.
  haveI : IsAffineHom j := isAffineHom_of_affine_separated j
  -- Presheaf description (Stacks 01XJ): `RŠĶ† j_* H ‚ČÖ sheafify(V ‚Ü¶ HŠĶ†((j_* I‚ÄĘ)(V)))`
  -- for any injective resolution `I` of `H`. Reduce to the vanishing of that sheafification.
  refine IsZero.of_iso ?_
    (higherDirectImage_iso_sheafify_presheafHomology j q (injectiveResolution H))
  set őĪ : X.ringCatSheaf.obj ‚ü∂ X.ringCatSheaf.obj := ūĚüô X.ringCatSheaf.obj with hőĪ
  set P := (pushforwardResolutionPresheafComplex j (injectiveResolution H)).homology q with hP
  -- Reflect `IsZero` through the faithful, zero-preserving forgetful functor `toSheaf`.
  apply Functor.isZero_of_faithful_preservesZeroMorphisms (SheafOfModules.toSheaf X.ringCatSheaf)
  -- Transport across the sheafification square
  -- `toSheaf ‚ąė sheafification ‚ČÖ presheafToSheaf ‚ąė toPresheaf`.
  refine IsZero.of_iso ?_ ((PresheafOfModules.sheafificationCompToSheaf őĪ).app P)
  set Q := (PresheafOfModules.toPresheaf X.ringCatSheaf.obj).obj P with hQ
  -- KEY VANISHING (genuine cohomological gap): the presheaf homology `Q` is a *zero object*
  -- over every affine open `W ‚äÜ X`, because `j‚ĀĽ¬ĻW` is affine (`j` is an affine morphism) and
  -- `affine_serre_vanishing` kills `HŠĶ†(j‚ĀĽ¬ĻW, H)` for `q ‚Č• 1`.
  have hSec : ‚ąÄ (W : TopologicalSpace.Opens X), IsAffineOpen W ‚Üí
      IsZero (Q.obj (Opposite.op W)) := by
    intro W hW
    -- Evaluate-at-`W` the presheaf complex; this functor preserves homology, so
    -- `Q.obj (op W) ‚ČÖ HŠĶ†(őď(W, f_* I‚ÄĘ)) = HŠĶ†(j‚ĀĽ¬ĻW, H)`, which vanishes for affine `j‚ĀĽ¬ĻW`.
    set GW := PresheafOfModules.toPresheaf X.ringCatSheaf.obj ‚čô
      (evaluation (TopologicalSpace.Opens X)ŠĶíŠĶĖ AddCommGrpCat).obj (Opposite.op W) with hGW
    set Kp := pushforwardResolutionPresheafComplex j (injectiveResolution H) with hKp
    refine IsZero.of_iso ?_ (GW.mapHomologyIso' (ComplexShape.up ‚Ąē) Kp q).symm
    -- The section complex `n ‚Ü¶ őď(W, f_* I^n) = őď(j‚ĀĽ¬ĻW, I^n)` is the image of the chosen
    -- injective resolution of `H` under the additive sections-over-`j‚ĀĽ¬ĻW` functor.
    have hcomplex : (GW.mapHomologicalComplex (ComplexShape.up ‚Ąē)).obj Kp
        = ((pushforwardSectionsFunctor j W).mapHomologicalComplex (ComplexShape.up ‚Ąē)).obj
            (injectiveResolution H).cocomplex :=
      rfl
    rw [hcomplex]
    -- `isoRightDerivedObj` recognises this homology as the `q`-th right derived sections
    -- functor `RŠĶ† őď(j‚ĀĽ¬ĻW, -)` applied to `H`, i.e. the absolute cohomology `HŠĶ†(j‚ĀĽ¬ĻW, H)`.
    refine IsZero.of_iso ?_ ((injectiveResolution H).isoRightDerivedObj
      (pushforwardSectionsFunctor j W) q).symm
    -- The sections functor `őď(j‚ĀĽ¬ĻW, -)` (here `pushforwardSectionsFunctor j W`, which is
    -- definitionally `sectionsFunctor (j ‚ĀĽ¬ĻŠĶĀ W)`) is corepresented by `jShriekOU (j ‚ĀĽ¬ĻŠĶĀ W)`, so its
    -- `q`-th right derived functor agrees with that of `Hom(jShriekOU (j ‚ĀĽ¬ĻŠĶĀ W), -)`.  This
    -- discharges the *geometric* corepresentability half of Bridge (1)/(2).
    refine IsZero.of_iso ?_ ((rightDerivedNatIso (sectionsFunctorCorepIso (j ‚ĀĽ¬ĻŠĶĀ W)) q).app H)
    -- RESIDUAL (Bridge 1/2 remainder + Bridge 2 vanishing): the `q`-th right derived functor of
    -- `Hom(jShriekOU (j ‚ĀĽ¬ĻŠĶĀ W), -)` vanishes on the quasi-coherent `H` for `q ‚Č• 1`.  Two pieces
    -- remain (see the task-result hand-off): (i) the homological-algebra identification
    -- `(preadditiveCoyoneda (op P)).rightDerived q ‚ČÖ Ext^q(P, -)` via the Hom-complex of an
    -- injective resolution (`InjectiveResolution.extAddEquivCohomologyClass` ‚ąė `homologyAddEquiv`),
    -- turning this into `IsZero (Ext (jShriekOU (j ‚ĀĽ¬ĻŠĶĀ W)) H q)`; and (ii) Serre vanishing for that
    -- `Ext` over the affine open `j ‚ĀĽ¬ĻŠĶĀ W` (a change-of-scheme transport of
    -- `cech_eq_cohomology_of_basis`/`affine_serre_vanishing` to a `BasisCovSystem` on the affine
    -- scheme `U`).
    -- Bridge (1)/(2) remainder DISCHARGED: `isZero_coyoneda_rightDerived_of_forall_ext_eq_zero`
    -- reduces the right-derived vanishing to `Ext`-vanishing.
    refine isZero_coyoneda_rightDerived_of_forall_ext_eq_zero (jShriekOU (j ‚ĀĽ¬ĻŠĶĀ W)) H q hq ?_
    intro e
    -- RESIDUAL (Bridge (2) Serre vanishing): every class of `Ext (jShriekOU (j‚ĀĽ¬ĻW)) H q` vanishes,
    -- `q ‚Č• 1`, `j‚ĀĽ¬ĻW` an affine open of the affine scheme `U`.  Transport along `U ‚ČÖ Spec őď(U,ūĚí™)`
    -- (`modulesIsoSpecExtTransport`) to `Ext (jShriekOU V') (ő¶ H) q` over `Spec őď U` and apply the
    -- now-unconditional `affine_serre_vanishing_general_open`, using the (still-to-build) jShriekOU
    -- transport iso `ő¶ (jShriekOU (j‚ĀĽ¬ĻW)) ‚ČÖ jShriekOU V'` and quasi-coherence of `ő¶ H`.
    sorry
  -- Since affine opens form a basis of `X`, every section of `Q` restricts to `0` on the
  -- affine opens contained in its domain, so `Q` is sectionwise locally zero and its
  -- sheafification vanishes.
  apply CategoryTheory.GrothendieckTopology.isZero_presheafToSheaf_of_sections_locally_zero
    (Opens.grothendieckTopology X) (Q := Q)
  intro U s
  refine ‚ü®{ arrows := fun {V} _ => ‚ąÉ W : TopologicalSpace.Opens X,
              IsAffineOpen W ‚ąß V ‚Č§ W ‚ąß W ‚Č§ U,
            downward_closed := ?_ }, ?_, ?_‚ü©
  ¬∑ rintro V V' g ‚ü®A, hA, hVA, hAU‚ü© h
    exact ‚ü®A, hA, le_trans (leOfHom h) hVA, hAU‚ü©
  ¬∑ -- membership in the opens topology: every point of `U` has an affine basis neighbourhood
    intro x hx
    obtain ‚ü®W, hWmem, hxW, hWU‚ü© :=
      (TopologicalSpace.Opens.isBasis_iff_nbhd.mp (Scheme.isBasis_affineOpens X)) hx
    exact ‚ü®W, homOfLE hWU, ‚ü®W, hWmem, le_refl W, hWU‚ü©, hxW‚ü©
  ¬∑ -- the restriction of `s` to a sieve member `V ‚Č§ A ‚Č§ U` (with `A` affine) factors through
    -- `Q.obj (op A) = 0`, hence vanishes.
    rintro V g ‚ü®A, hA, hVA, hAU‚ü©
    haveI : Subsingleton (ToType (Q.obj (Opposite.op A))) :=
      AddCommGrpCat.subsingleton_of_isZero (hSec A hA)
    have hgfac : g.op = (homOfLE hAU).op ‚Čę (homOfLE hVA).op := by
      rw [‚Üź op_comp]; congr 1
    rw [hgfac, Q.map_comp, ConcreteCategory.comp_apply,
      Subsingleton.elim ((ConcreteCategory.hom (Q.map (homOfLE hAU).op)) s) 0, map_zero]

/-- **Composition formula for higher direct images across an open immersion** (pinned
declaration; blueprint `lem:open_immersion_pushforward_comp`, part (2); Stacks
`lemma-relative-affine-vanishing`).

Let `j : U ‚Ü™ X` be an open immersion of an affine open `U` into a separated scheme `X`,
and `f : X ‚ü∂ S` any morphism. For every quasi-coherent `O_U`-module `H` and every `k ‚Č• 0`:
```
  R^k f_*(j_* H) ‚ČÖ R^k (f ‚ąė j)_* H.
```
Proof route: choose an injective resolution `H ‚Üí I‚ÄĘ` in `U.Modules`; apply `j_*`
degreewise to get an `f_*`-acyclic resolution `j_* I‚ÄĘ` of `j_* H`
(`higherDirectImage_openImmersion_acyclic` for `j_*`-acyclicity, extended to
`f_*`-acyclicity via the same Serre-vanishing argument on `U ‚ą© f‚ĀĽ¬ĻV`); then
`Functor.rightDerivedIsoOfAcyclicResolution` with `G = (pushforward f)` and the identity
`(pushforward f) ‚ąė (pushforward j) = pushforward (j ‚Čę f)` give the stated isomorphism. -/
noncomputable def higherDirectImage_openImmersion_comp
    [HasInjectiveResolutions X.Modules] [HasInjectiveResolutions U.Modules]
    (j : U ‚ü∂ X) [IsOpenImmersion j] [IsAffine U] [X.IsSeparated]
    (f : X ‚ü∂ S) (H : U.Modules) (hH : H.IsQuasicoherent) (k : ‚Ąē) :
    higherDirectImage f k ((pushforward j).obj H) ‚ČÖ
      higherDirectImage (j ‚Čę f) k H := by
  haveI : IsAffineHom j := isAffineHom_of_affine_separated j
  -- Structural plan (all categorical building blocks below are verified to exist):
  --   ‚ÄĘ `G := Scheme.Modules.pushforward f` is additive and preserves finite limits
  --     (`inferInstance`), so `Functor.rightDerivedIsoOfAcyclicResolution` applies to it.
  --   ‚ÄĘ The pushed-forward injective resolution `K := (pushforward j).mapHomologicalComplex I‚ÄĘ`
  --     is a candidate acyclic resolution of `j_* H = (pushforward j).obj H`.
  --   ‚ÄĘ `pushforwardComp j f : pushforward j ‚čô pushforward f ‚ČÖ pushforward (j ‚Čę f)` turns
  --     `H^k(G(K))` into `H^k((j ‚Čę f)_* I‚ÄĘ) = R^k (j ‚Čę f)_* H`.
  -- RESIDUAL (genuine cohomological gaps, handed off ‚ÄĒ each depends on Part (1)'s residual):
  --   (a) `K` is exact in positive degrees and resolves `j_* H` (i.e. `j_* I‚ÄĘ` is a
  --       resolution of `j_* H`) ‚ÄĒ this is `j_*`-acyclicity, the content of
  --       `higherDirectImage_openImmersion_acyclic` applied to each `I‚ĀŅ` and to `H`.
  --   (b) each term `(pushforward j).obj (I‚ĀŅ)` is `(pushforward f)`-acyclic
  --       (`Functor.IsRightAcyclic`), i.e. `R^k f_*(j_* I‚ĀŅ) = 0` for `k ‚Č• 1` ‚ÄĒ the same
  --       Serre-vanishing argument on the affine `U ‚ą© f‚ĀĽ¬ĻV` (generalises Part (1) from
  --       `j_*` to `f_*` via the presheaf description on `f‚ĀĽ¬ĻV`).
  -- Then `Functor.rightDerivedIsoOfAcyclicResolution (pushforward f) K (j_* H) e (a) k`
  -- composed with the `pushforwardComp` transport gives the stated iso.
  sorry

